defaultSarah is a 17 year old who was refer
defaultred for psychiatric services when she was rescued by a passer-by from attempting to throw herself off a bridge. Sarah is the sole 
defaultcarer
default for her mother and younger siblings and has been finding it difficult to cope with her studies and responsibilities. Sar
defaultah’s mother refuses to engage with support services and Sarah’s psychiatrist has been trying to refer Sarah to the local authority for a child in need assessment under the Children Act 1989 but was not having any success in doing so. Sarah’s mother told he
defaultr that she could not return to the house and Sarah was facing street homelessness. 
defaultStreetlegal
default wrote a pre-action protocol letter challenging the local authority’s failure to carried out the assessment and provide Section 20 accommodation. Following this t
defaulthe local authority accommodated Sarah whilst an assessment was being carried out by social services. The local authority then accepted a full Section 20 duty under the Children Act 1989 to accommodate and look after Sarah. Sarah would have been unable to v
defaultentilate her case without the expert help of legal aid lawyers.
