defaultAmber is a 20 year old who has two children aged 1 and 2. Amber’s mother was diagnosed with cancer in January 2010 when she was pregnant with her second child. Amber’s mother asked her to lea
defaultve as there was not enough space in the house for her to stay. Amber approached the local authority to make a housing application and was told that she could only apply for private rented accommodation and was not entitled to temporary accommodation. The L
defaultocal Authority however did not offer any private accommodation and each time Amber called up she was told someone would call back but they never did. Amber’s mother passed away in November 2010 and has still not been provided with any accommodation. Amber’
defaults mother left her housing association to Amber’s older brother with whom Amber has always had a difficult relationship. Amber’s brother was 
defaultpressurising
default her to leave and additionally there was an insect infestation in the house that he was refusing to addr
defaultess. Amber’s doctor wrote a letter concerning Amber’s skin condition and the local authority had still not provided her with any accommodation. 
defaultStreetlegal
default wrote a letter to the local authority proposing to commence judicial review proceedings if they did 
defaultnot provide Amber with emergency temporary accommodation. Amber and her children were then provided with suitable accommodation. Amber was a particularly vulnerable young person who would have had little prospect of rectifying her situation without the ass
defaultistance of a legal aid lawyer.
