default 
defaultThe Home Of
defaultfice refuse to engage with numerous pre-action correspondence and we have no choice but to lodge a claim 
defaultincluding
default an urgent application for interim relief from the court. The judge considering the application orders that the interview be postponed pending
default the outcome of the psychiatric assessment. Subsequently, we are contacted by Treasury Solicitors. We receive an apology for the lack of correspondence and advised that the decision to refuse our requests were made by a ‘new member of staff’ and the pre-ac
defaulttion correspondence had not reached a senior official in time. The case is conceded and there is no need for the case to go up to a judge to consider whether permission be granted.
